<br>
Magicians summon elementals from alternate planes to do their bidding. These elementals are 'bound' (charmed) into service, either by force or by partnership (again, roleplayishly, depending on how you'd describe the relationship between you and your pets). This binding is unbreakable, it is perminent (til zone, death of pet/you). Advantages over regular enchanter charm is that our pets are not dependant upon a creature existing in this plane for us to charm. Disadvantage is that our pets are not anywhere near as strong as the creatures in our plane.<br>
<br>
I know a lot of people aren't going to see it that way, and I don't vouch for it as anything other than a casual observation/comparison. There is no argument here that we already have dire charm, but the parallels are quite similar, dependant on the understanding that our pets are creatures of their own to begin with (unlike necro pets which are born of the Necromancer). <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=52886">Rhasin Firestorm</A><BR>
Conjurer of the 57th Season<BR>
